   Date: Tue, 12 Sep 89 23:50 EDT
   From: Barry Margolin &lt;barmar@think.com&gt;

   ...  The final answer is that MILNET sites simply aren't yet
   required to run resolvers.  There is a schedule of conversion to
   the domain system on the Arpanet and MILNET, and according to that
   schedule resolvers are still optional on MILNET.

According to RFC-1031, the deadline for conversion of MILNET hosts to
the DNS is next month (October 1989), at which point the NIC host
table will supposedly be discontinued.  Given the recent discussion,
this seems unlikely, but as far as I know this is still the official
schedule.  Anybody have any updates on this?

--Rob Austein, MIT

